Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows impression of a fine textile as well as some fibres of a unturned string, which can also be seen in the break. The front shows a small part of a seal impression. Visible is a standing line and legs and apron of a standing male figure, facing to the left. Left of the figure a further sign that is probably a mn (Y5).
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
